notes.body: Hello Madhu,       ​Greetings from PharmEasy!     With regard to your order #655952473076563968, I can see your order is in process and the medicines are being arranged.      Also, I noticed the requested medicine VALENT 40MG STRIP OF 10 TABLETS is limited in stock. We will try to deliver your order as per the estimated delivery date between 07th December 2025 to 09th December 2025.     ​As per the system, our partner retailer is trying to arrange 3 quantities. We are unable to commit to a time frame. However, as per the system, it is expected to be arranged by 08th December 2025.      However, you have the option to delete the unavailable medicine to avoid further delays in the delivery. Or you can wait till the medicines are arranged.     Please confirm if you wish to delete the said medicine. If the said medicine is deleted, there is a possibility that there might be some changes in the delivery charges and/or the promo code if applied.      Please be assured that your feedback regarding avoiding the splitting of orders into multiple shipments, based on medicine availability, has been duly noted and will be shared with the relevant team for future improvements.  Awaiting your response.     Regards,  Sandhya Nackwal
notes.body_html:
Hello Madhu,

​Greetings from PharmEasy!

With regard to your order #655952473076563968, I can see your order is in process and the medicines are being arranged. 

Also, I noticed the requested medicine VALENT 40MG STRIP OF 10 TABLETS is limited in stock. We will try to deliver your order as per the estimated delivery date between 07th December 2025 to 09th December 2025.

​As per the system, our partner retailer is trying to arrange 3 quantities. We are unable to commit to a time frame. However, as per the system, it is expected to be arranged by 08th December 2025. 

However, you have the option to delete the unavailable medicine to avoid further delays in the delivery. Or you can wait till the medicines are arranged.

Please confirm if you wish to delete the said medicine. If the said medicine is deleted, there is a possibility that there might be some changes in the delivery charges and/or the promo code if applied. 

Please be assured that your feedback regarding avoiding the splitting of orders into multiple shipments, based on medicine availability, has been duly noted and will be shared with the relevant team for future improvements.
Awaiting your response.

Regards,
Sandhya Nackwal

notes.body_html:
Hello Geetha,

Greetings from PharmEasy!
 
This email is with reference to the concern raised for order #655087635980529664-33422.
 
We have received an update from our logistics team. As per the update, your order has been delivered to you. Please accept my sincere apology for the inconvenience caused to you. We have shared the required feedback with the delivery agent and we will make sure that such instances are not repeated in the future.
 
Please consider this as a one-off instance as we aim to provide the best of services to our customers and such instances are very rare.
​
We are marking the ticket as resolved. PharmEasy looks forward to bettering your experience in the future.

For any further assistance, please reopen this ticket or reach out to us through our support channels, in the App or website, listed in the 'Need Help' section. 
 
Thank you for choosing PharmEasy. Have a great day ahead!

Regards, 
PharmEasy

I always order from Pharm Easy and every time I am sent alternative
medicines or medicines with different types. I am facing a lot of trouble
from you in every order. I am seeing that you do not call the concerned
customer in any way regarding this and their prior consent is not even
taken. I do not think it is right that you have to make full payment and
wait for eight days for the medicine and then cancel it and wait for a
refund. I am facing unnecessary trouble and I want you to cancel the order
at Delhi rate. Also, when you are taking the order, you order the same
medicine and ask the customer care to call from the senior, but the call
does not even come.

notes.body:
Dear Sandhya,

I had ordered two products:

1. Ketomac Shampoo

2. Aloe Vera Juice

Later, I received a call from PharmEasy where I was informed about the
benefits of Neem Juice and was told that two bottles were available under
an offer. However, when I checked, even a single bottle had a similar
offer. So, I cancelled and modified the order again.

The payment was made only for those two original products, and the refund
has also been processed accordingly.

My concern is that the information provided that the offer applies only
when proceeding with payment — is misleading and incorrect.

Please find the attachment for your reference.

Atif
9111788618

helpdesk_ticket.description:
To the Grievance Redressal Team,
PharmEasy / National Consumer Helpline
I am writing to formally register a complaint regarding the severe lapse in service for my recent order, ID- 655229393197072384 placed on 3rd dec.

1. Factual Summary of the Issue

• Order Details: The full order was scheduled to be delivered in two parts. The first part was placed under your "Express Delivery" service, which commits to delivery within a specified window.
• Breach of Commitment: The confirmed delivery window for the first part was [dec 4th between 8:00 PM and 10:00 PM. As of now I have not received delivery of my order also they have cancelled my first order post complaining to their Grievance officer. I have placed new order but still that is not delivered and it was promised to be delivered on 5th dec (today) but this is really frustrating it has not been delivered yet.
• Failure of Communication: Despite repeated assurances from your customer service executives since yesterday that I would receive a confirmatory call regarding the delivery, no call has been received to date, leaving the delivery status pending and uncertain.
2. Aggravating Circumstances & Breach of Trust

• Premium Customer Status: I am a Premium Customer holding a valid subscription with PharmEasy, signifying a commitment to preferred service, which has been clearly violated in this instance.
• Previous Instance of Failure: This is not an isolated incident. I experienced a similar service failure and significant delay (4-5 days) on a prior order, indicating a systemic issue with your logistics and delivery management.
• Violation of Express Service Terms: By failing to deliver within the specified express window, you have breached the fundamental condition of the Express Delivery service for which I paid and relied upon.

3. Expected Resolution

I require the following immediate action:

1. Immediate Confirmation and Delivery: The first part of Order ID- 655608261363892224 must be delivered as promised immediately.

2. Compensation: Given the repeated inconvenience, the failed service commitment (Express Delivery), and the lack of reliable communication, I demand appropriate compensation for the direct failure to provide the paid-for service.

3. Importance of medicines: The medicines Sugar, blood pressure and other diseases, who will take the responsibility for this delay?

Kindly treat this matter with the utmost urgency. I expect a formal response and confirmation of resolution within 48 hours. Failing a satisfactory resolution, I will be compelled to escalate this complaint further to the relevant Consumer Commissions and public platforms, including social media, to warn others about this recurrent lapse in service.

Thank you for your prompt attention to this critical matter

Sent from my iPhone
--

With regards to your order #654316280390090752-47590, I am sorry to know you have not received the medicine you ordered, ALFUNOL D STRIP OF 10 TABLETS, quantity of 2. I am highlighting your concern to the Escalation team, and our team will investigate it. If the medicine is found to be missing, the refund amount of Rs. 317.68 will be initiated. Post initiation of the refund, the amount will be credited to your PharmEasy wallet in 24 hours.     You can expect the resolution within 24 to 48 hours. We will get back to you with an update once we receive it.      Further, was the parcel intact, or was there any damage from the outside at the time of delivery?     I appreciate your patience in the meantime.     Regards,  Habiba
